Following is the text of the U.S.
steel report from the Commerce Department:  The U.S. Census Bureau announced today that preliminary May
steel imports were $2.8 billion (2.4 million metric tons).  This
was an increase of $0.2 billion (0.1 million metric tons) from
the preliminary April totals of $2.6 billion  The May change in steel imports based on metric tonnage
reflected an increase primarily in blooms, billets, and slabs.
Increases occurred primarily with Brazil and  Russia .  The year to date final statistics through April 2011 showed
steel imports of  8.1 million metric tons compared with 6.7
million metric tons through April 2010. The largest commodity
increases occurred primarily in blooms, billets, an  Notes:  The data in this report are preliminary and subject to revisions.  Analysis of recent months for steel product imports indicates
the value of preliminary data should equal about 96 percent of
the final value reported in the regular monthly trade statistics
